## What Makes Equipment "Signature"

### Personal Connection

Signature equipment requires personal significance beyond mechanical stats:

**Inherited:** Passed down through generations, carrying family history
**Earned:** Won through great deeds or personal quests
**Created:** Forged personally or commissioned from master craftsman
**Bonded:** Found early in adventuring career, carried through all challenges

Random loot sword #17 doesn't become signature equipment. The blade you inherited from your mentor, that saved your life in your first real battle, that bears your personal inscription—that becomes signature.

### Cannot Be Permanently Lost

The defining feature: signature equipment always returns to you eventually.

**Stolen:** You recover it through quests
**Destroyed:** It can be reforged with appropriate resources and time
**Separated:** Narrative ensures reunion within reasonable timeframe

This doesn't mean signature equipment is indestructible or un-loseable. It means permanent loss isn't an option—temporary separation creates story opportunities, but signature equipment always comes back.

Game Masters shouldn't abuse this: don't constantly steal signature equipment for cheap drama. But knowing it cannot be permanently lost lets players invest emotionally without fear.

